order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">election law</a> to regulate Facebook, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0though I =
can=E2=80=99t say any of them strike me as great. Still it=E2=80=99s the ri=
ght basic idea. Figure out what you don=E2=80=99t like about Facebook=E2=80=
=99s dominance and then regulate that, rather than just equating bigness wi=
th=C2=A0<em>antitrust</em>.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24317788.267871/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9iaWRlbi13ZWlnaHMtbmV3LWV4ZWN1dGl2ZS1vcmRlci1y=
ZXN0cmFpbmluZy1iaWctYnVzaW5lc3MtMTE2MjUwMDc4MDQ_bW9kPWl0cF93c2omcnU9eWFob28=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7669275b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">here=E2=80=99s this</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Biden administration is developing an executive or=
der directing agencies to strengthen oversight of industries that they perc=
eive to be dominated by a small number of companies, a wide-ranging attempt=
 to rein in big business power across the economy, according to people fami=
liar with the plans.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The executive order, w=
hich President Biden could sign as soon as next week, would direct regulato=
rs of industries from airlines to agriculture to rethink their rule-making =
process to inject more competition and to give consumers, workers and suppl=
iers more rights to challenge large producers.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">The goal is to broaden the way policy makers approach business concentr=
ation in the U.S., going beyond conventional antitrust enforcement focused =
on blocking big mergers. For example, companies in industries controlled by=
 a small number of big firms might face new rules for disclosing fees to co=
nsumers or for their relationships with suppliers, the people familiar with=
 the effort said.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Seems right!=
 Or not, I mean; I guess it depends on how you feel about big business gene=
rally. But if you feel bad about some big business=C2=A0<em>specifically</e=
m>, addressing that in a specific way =E2=80=94=C2=A0rather than assuming t=
hat big business is exclusively an antitrust problem =E2=80=94=C2=A0seems l=
ike the way to go.</p>
